        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 4 at 7:03PM EDT until September 4 at 7:30PM EDT by NWS State College PA</headline>
        <description>SVRCTP

The National Weather Service in State College PA has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
East central Columbia County in central Pennsylvania...

* Until 730 PM EDT.

* At 702 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Mifflinville,
moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Bloomsburg, Berwick, Mifflinville, Lightstreet, Almedia, Espy, Lime
Ridge, Briar Creek, Orangeville, Stillwater, and Bloomsburg
University.

For those driving on Interstate 80, this includes areas between the
Buckhorn and Mifflinville exits, specifically from mile markers 234
to 241.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay inside a well built structure and keep away from windows.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will send your report to the National Weather Service
office in State College PA.</instruction>
